  "prompt": "What are consequences of Brexit thus far?",
  "response": "Brexit, the United Kingdom's withdrawal from the European Union, has had several significant consequences:\n\nEconomic Impacts:\n1. Reduced trade with EU countries\n2. Increased bureaucracy and trade barriers\n3. Higher costs for businesses\n4. Decreased foreign investment\n5. Some companies relocating from UK to EU\n\nLabor Market Effects:\n1. Reduced EU immigration\n2. Labor shortages in certain sectors (agriculture, hospitality)\n3. Changes in work visa requirements\n4. Challenges for UK citizens working in EU countries\n\nPolitical Consequences:\n1. Strained UK-EU relations\n2. Scottish independence movement strengthened\n3. Northern Ireland protocol complications\n4. Changes in diplomatic relationships\n\nConsumer Effects:\n1. Higher prices for imported goods\n2. More complex travel procedures\n3. Reduced consumer choices\n4. Additional paperwork for cross-border transactions\n\nFinancial Services:\n1. Loss of \"passporting\" rights for financial institutions\n2. Reduced London's status as a global financial center\n3. Some financial services moving to other EU cities\n\nAcademic and Research:\n1. Reduced participation in EU research programs\n2. Challenges for student exchanges\n3. Decreased international collaboration\n\nThese impacts continue to evolve, and the full long-term consequences are still unfolding.",
